  documents into a structured and verifiable set of requirements for a sleep
  questionnaire application. My approach involved first identifying and reading
  available documents, noting that binary files like  and  could
  not be processed directly. I then decided to create a dedicated
   directory to archive the original source materials. For
  the new requirements, I made a key decision to split the information into two
  distinct Markdown files:  for a high-level overview of
  product, functional, and technical requirements, and
  for the granular details of the questionnaire's structure, including specific
  questions, conditional logic, scoring mechanisms, and diagnostic criteria.
  This structured outcome provides a clear, consolidated reference for
  developing and validating the sleep questionnaire application."
